Description: This is an unusual version of the Schecter Stargazer 12 with a maple fretboard and Fender-ish black blocks, rather than the usual rosewood fretboard. Looks great with the black finish. Ash body and set (not bolt) maple neck. The wide nut on this guitar makes it much more easily playable than a lot of electric 12s. And the coil splitting gives a nice variety of tones. This particular guitar is used, but is in good shape. It's not perfect or a "mint" collector's item, as there are minor marks in the finish and signs of use, and a small chip at the end of the headstock (see photo). But it's in good working order, hasn't been abused, and looks very nice. Construction: Set-neckScale length: 25-1/2"Body: AshNeck: MapleFingerboard: MapleFrets: 22 jumboInlays: BlockPickups: Schecter SuperRock Custom AlnicoElectronics: 2 Vol/2 Tone with push/pull coil-splitting, 3-way pickup selectorBridge: Diamond Adjustable-12Binding: WhiteTuners: GroverHardware: ChromeGig bag included.
